                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1113">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.51/1212: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in El Salvador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-10T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 10, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>159. You may, in your discretion, inform the appropriate Salvadoran authority
                    that the Department does not support the views expressed by Mr. Renwick,
                    regarding the recent Salvadoran bond settlement, as set forth in the enclosure
                    to your despatch no. 1599 of May 20, 1944.<note n="98" xml:id="d1113fn98"
                        >Despatch and its enclosures not printed.</note> The Department has no
                    objection to the plan already negotiated between the Salvadoran representatives
                    and the Foreign Bondholders Council; and it earnestly hopes that the Salvadoran
                    Government, on its part, will maintain the expressed intention of the previous
                    Salvadoran Administration<note n="99" xml:id="d1113fn99">For information on the
                        revolutionary change of government in El Salvador, see <ref
                            target="#pg_1087">pp. 1087</ref> ff.</note> to carry out this plan.
                    Further <pb facs="1140" n="1126" xml:id="pg_1126"/> background material is being
                    forwarded by airmail for your information.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
